body:
### Describe the bug

I wrote a custom type with generic parameter
```
class Operation<T> {
  String name;
  String op;
  T value;
}
```
a custom annotation 
```
interface @OperationParam {
  String value();
  Class<?> boundedType();
}
```
and custom ParamConverterProvider + ParamConverter
```
public class OperationConverter<T> implements ParamConverter<Operation<T>>
{
  ParamConverter<T> valueConverter;
  String name;
}

@Provider
public class OperationConverterProvider implements ParamConverterProvider {
  @Override
  public <T> ParamConverter<T> getConverter(Class<T> rawType, Type genericType, Annotation[] annotations) {
    if (rawType.isAssignableFrom(Operation.class)) {
      OperationParam  annot = getOperationParamAnnot(annotations);
      String name = /* extract information from annotation or method parameters */;
      ParamConverter<T> valueConverter = /* extract information from annotation or method parameters to create right implementation */;
      return new OperationConverter<T>(name, valueConverter);
    }
    return null;
  }
}
```

Given
```
@RegisterRestClient(configKey = "client")
interface Client {
  @Path("call-with-bean")
  @GET
  void callWithBean(@BeanParam MultipleFilterRuleBean bean);
}

class MultipleFilterRuleBean {
  @OperationParam(value = "int_from_annot")
  @QueryParam("i")
  public Operation<Integer> integer;
  @OperationParam(value = "enum_from_annot", boundedType = MyEnum.class)
  @QueryParam("e")
  public Operation myEnum;
}
```
in my `OperationConverterProvider` the only available annotation in `annotations` param is `@BeanParam`, not `@OperationParam` not `@QueryParam` are available as I expected.

### Expected behavior

First error: accessing annotations on every annotated properties and not client only annotations attached to @RestClient method.

### Actual behavior

as described above

### How to Reproduce?

- https://github.com/luca-bassoricci/custom-provider/tree/main : reproducer for annotation problem

